Statements: Whenever we have to make decisions, we use statements
            1. if statement [fails to handle false scenario]
            if(condition)
            {
               This will execute only if condition is true
            }


            2. multiple if statement -> to make multiple decisions[slow performance and fails to handle false scenario]

            3. if-else statement
                   if(condition)
                        {
                           This will execute only if condition is true
                        }
                        else
                        {
                           This will execute only if condition is false
                        }

            if-else[Just to check one condition with positive and negative scenarios]
            if-else if statement[Check multiple conditions, slower]
            switch statement [Check multiple conditions, faster]
                             range
                             &&
                             long, float, double, boolean data types
